-- Obama Nominates Top Justice National Security Official
-- B y   P h i l   M a t t i n g l y
-- 2013-09-10T22:19:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-10/obama-nominates-top-justice-national-security-official.html
U.S. President Barack Obama will
nominate John P. Carlin as the top national security official at
the Justice Department, the White House said.  Carlin, if confirmed, would replace  Lisa Monaco , who left
the Justice Department in March to serve as Obama’s top homeland
security adviser. He has been serving as the acting assistant
attorney general in charge of the national security division
since Monaco’s departure.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Phil Mattingly in Washington at 
 pmattingly@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
